The huge contraption can be found at the world's biggest single coal excavation site, the Bogatyr Mine near the city of Ekibastuz in Kazakhstan.

Incredibly, the diameter of the saw alone spans nearly 12 metres - about the same height as a four- storey building - while a single machine can cost up to £66million to produce.

Its hulking mass and height of 45 metres means it can only travel one mile every three hours.

