'I was not scared to get so close but was more in awe of its power and design.'

About 40 million tons of coal is taken from the Bogatyr mines every year, accounting for 40 per cent of the nation's coal output.

In 1985 it entered the Guinness Book of Records for being the world's largest single coal mine when 56.8 million tonnes of coal were taken from the ground.

